title: Start
body: Good to see you again! \nLet's take a look at how you did in the second session \n Let's start by looking at participation [[Ok|participation_1]]

title: participation
body: You participated more this time

title: participation_1
body: What do you think changed? Did you participate more or less? [[more|participation_2]] [[less|participation_2]][[about the same|participation_2]]

title: overlap_1
body: Great! Now let's move on to overlaps. [[Okay|overlap_2]]

title: overlap_2
body: In the recent +session_time+ minute session you overlapped others +overlap_me+ times. Others overlapped you +overlap_others+ times[[Interesting|overlap_3]][[Sounds about right|overlap_3]][[I don't believe it..|overlap_4]]

title: overlap_3
body: Looks like there was less overlap this time.\\nNice job listening to others![[Thanks!|turntaking_1]]

title: overlap_5
body: My information isn't always correction. Which part did you think was off?[[My overlaps|overlap_6]][[Others overlapping me|overlaps6]]

title: overlap_6
body: Were the numbers too low or too high? [[too low|overlap_7]][[too_high|overlap_7]]

title: overlap_7
body: Thanks for the feedback!\\nWe'll check that for next time.\\nMeanwhile, let's talk about turn taking.[[Let's do it!|turntaking_1]]

title: turntaking_1
body: This turn taking graph shows how often you spoke directly after someone in the group.\\nFeel free to click the graph to see each person![[

title: overlap_4
body: Looks like there was more overlap this time.\\nResearch shows that overlaps might indicate greater rapport between a team[[Cool|turntaking_1]]

title: turntaking_
body: Looks like you and +turntaking_most+ really struck a conversation!\\nYou spoke after each other the most in both sessions. [[Cool, didn't know that| ]]

title: turntaking_
body: Nice job discussing with everyone in the group!\\n[[Thanks!|valence_1]]

title: turntaking_
body: Looks like you didn't get as much of a chance to talk to +turntaking_least_name+

title: valence_1
body: Cool, now onto valence which shows how positive or negative your facial expressions were.[[Let's see it!|valence_2 valence_3]]

title: valence_2
body: Looks like the group was bursting with positivity!\\nThat's awesome, keep it up.[[heck yeah|sharedsmile_1]]

title: valence_3
body: Looks like thing might not have been going too well.\\nWas anything up? [[No|valence_5]][[tough topic| ]][[disagreements| ]][[something else| ]]

title: valence_4
body: Riding the neutral vibes. Good place to be. [[yup!|sharedsmile_1]][[I wouldn't say it was neutral...|]]

title: sharedsmile_1
body: How smiley were you feeling during the call? [[:)|sharedsmile_3]][[:/|sharedsmile_4]]

title: valence_5
body: Ok\\nLet's talked about shared smiles then[[sure|sharedsmile_1]]

title: valence_6
body: Sorry to hear... Disagreements are tough to handle[[yeah...|sharedsmile_1]]

title: sharedsmile_3
body: You smiled a lot!\\nAnd +sharedsmile_most_name+ had the good fortune of sharing these smiles with you. Nice job building rapport![[Woo!|finish_1]]

title: finish_1
body: That's all I have! Hope you have a good rest of the day. :)

title: sharedsmile_4
body: You smiled more than you think!
